textBeforeTable: The Sports Network/Fathead.com FCS Top-25 College Football Poll #15/16 Old Dominion will square off against #9/10 James Madison at noon Saturday in the revival of the Oyster Bowl in front of the Comcast SportsNetwork cameras. Moving up seven spaces in the Coaches Poll after the victory over the Wildcats, the Monarchs are also joined by No. 10 James Madison, No. 11 New Hampshire, No. 12 Maine, No. 14 Towson, No. 20 Delaware, and No. 21 William & Mary. The Monarchs, who jumped six spots in the TSN Poll following its 37-14 win at Villanova last weekend, are also joined by seven other CAA schools in the poll including No. 8 Maine, No. 9 James Madison, No. 10 New Hampshire, No. 13 Towson, No. 18 William & Mary, and No. 21 Delaware. NORFOLK, Va. -- The Old Dominion Football Monarchs moved up to No. 15 in The Sports Network/Fathead.com Top 25 Poll and to No. 16 in the FCS Coaches Poll it was announced Monday afternoon.
